 in the late nineteenth century. By exploring the meetings between Buddhists and Muslims along the Silk Road from Iran to China over more than a millennium, Johan Elverskog reveals that this long encounter was actually one of profound cross-cultural exchange in which two religious traditions were not only enriched but transformed in many ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBuddhismxRelationsxIslam. 0aBuddhismxRelationszIslam. 0aBuddhismxSilk RoadxHistory. 0aBuddhismzSilk RoadxHistory. 0aHISTORYxAsiaxGeneral. 0aIslamxRelationsxBuddhism. 0aIslamxSilk RoadxHistory. 0aIslamzSilk RoadxHistory. 4aMiddle Eastern. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh  aAfrican Studies.  aAsian Studies.  aHistory.  aMiddle Eastern Studies.  aReligion.  aReligious Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package Complete Collectionz978311041345808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn Press eBook Package World Historyz978311041347208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311045954840uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978081220531240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812205312423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780812205312/original  a978-3-11-041345-8  Penn Press eBook Package Complete Collection  a978-3-11-041347-2  Penn Press eBook Package World History  a978-3-11-045954-8  University of Pennsylvania Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagec2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  a